en_317763_0	Security Force troops in the Wanni during the just-concluded feast of Our Lady of Madu in Madu, Mannnar cooperated closely with Policemen and ensured maximum security for the conduct of this historic feast, confirmed to have been attended by an estimated crowd of 340,000 devotees of all ethnicity on the final day (August 15) of the feast.
en_317763_1	The tight and direct security network closely supervised by the Commander, Security Forces-Wanni Major General Jagath Gunawardena functioned smoothly with no inconvenience to the visiting devotees visiting this one of the holiest Catholic shrines in the island.
en_317763_2	Sri Lanka Army has been providing security for the sacred event for many years in coordination with the Police.
en_317763_3	613 Brigade Commander Colonel R.K.N.C Jayawardane carried out Security measures under the guidance and supervision of the General Officer Commanding of the 61 Division, Major General R.K.G.S Ketakumbura.
en_317763_4	Troops representing 6 Sri Lanka Light Infantry (SLLI), 24 Sri Lanka Light Infantry (SLLI), 21 Sri Lanka Sinha Regiment (SLSR), 7 Vijayabahu Infantry Regiment (VIR) and 10 (Volunteer) Gemunu Watch (GW) during the day and night provided the necessary security to the premises and devotees.
en_317763_5	The Shrine of Our Lady of Madhu is a Roman Catholic Shrine in Mannar district.
en_317763_6	This sacred shrine having a history over 400 years, yet keeps noble mark in the hearts of thousands of pilgrims representing the Sri Lankan Catholic community and other communities during the Feast where they pay homage to the Lady of Madu and is a well-known place of devotion for both Tamil and Sinhalese Catholics.
